item.title: Major insurers plan to drop Kia, Hyundai car models' coverage due to thefts

Both State Farm and Progressive confirmed with CNN that they no longer write policies for some Kia and Hyundai models manufactured between 2015 and 2019. In September 2022, the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IHHS) and the Highway Loss Data Institute (HLDI) reported that vehicle theft claims for 2015-19 Hyundai and Kia vehicles were nearly twice as common as the Dodge Charger SRT Hellcat.
